summary: LETTER FROM TONY  PRIESGEN , VICE PRESIDENT OF TRITON CORPORATION, OPPOSING THOSE PROVISIONS OF EARLY WARNING REPORTING (EWR) REGULATION THAT REQUIRES MANUFACTURERS THAT PRODUCE OVER 500 SMALL-TO-MEDIUM TRAILERS (THOSE WITH A GROSS VEHICLE WEIGHT RATING (GVWR) OF UNDER 26000 POUNDS) TO SUBMIT COMPREHENSIVE EARLY WARNING REPORTS TO NHTSA. MR. PRIESGEN CLAIMED THAT SUCH REPORTING WOULD PUT HIM AND MANY OF HIS COLLEAGES IN TRAILER INDUSTRY OUT OF BUSINESS.  *AK
